AirJam redefines music accessibility by transforming standard webcams into virtual instruments, effectively democratizing music education through a zero-cost, touchless interface. Under the hood, this seamless experience is powered by a high-performance hybrid architecture: a Python backend leveraging MediaPipe for millisecond-latency 3D hand tracking and a custom physics engine for velocity smoothing, coupled with a highly optimized NumPy/SimpleAudio synthesis pipeline for rich, real-time sound. The frontend complements this raw power with a polished, 60FPS HTML5 Canvas game loop and reactive particle systems, proving that complex computer vision and professional-grade aesthetics can converge to create a frictionless, gamified learning platform.
